\f0\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\i \cb2 BofA Securities, Research Division
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 Can I just ask on turkey specifically. So we know that turkey was a $0.25 headwind to fiscal '23 and then roughly a $0.15 headwind to fiscal '24. So could you just help us bridge the '25 impact? So what was the full year turkey headwind or tailwind to earnings in '25?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 John Ghingo
\f0\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\i \cb2 President & Director
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 Just to give you a little bit of color on turkey. So I mean, in general, we saw a lot of, I'll say, increased costs in turkey in 2025. We were able to land on our ground turkey business, the pricing we needed to, to cover that in terms of how that played out for the year. Those first half pressures really hit us quite hard, and we were able to balance that back in the second half and offset those first half headwinds with the improved results in the back half.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 In terms of whole birds, they did come in somewhat better than expected compared to our original outlook from fiscal 2025. But it was obviously a very, I'll call it, volatile year on turkey. And we weathered it quite well from a competitive standpoint and the recovery in the back half of the year. All in, it was a benefit in 2025.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Yasmine Deswandhy
\f0\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\i \cb2 BofA Securities, Research Division
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 Okay. Great. That's helpful. And then on raw materials inflation, you had said last earnings that, I think, 3Q was roughly 400 bps. How much was it in 4Q? And how should we think about it in '26 on a quarterly basis, given there's typically some seasonality there?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Paul Kuehneman
\f0\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\i \cb2 Interim Chief Financial Officer & Controller
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 Yes. Thanks, Yasmine, for your question. In quarter 4 was a 500 basis points of raw material cost inflation during the fourth quarter. For the second part of the question, I direct you to Jess and having more internal discussions there.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
